Success Nwogu, Abuja The Deputy National Chairman, (North) of the Peoples Democratic Party, Senator Suleiman Nazif, has boasted that the party will win the 2023 presidential election and get majority members in both chambers of the National Assembly. He also said he was confident that the party would bounce back to power in the North following its improved performance in the 2019 general elections. He claimed that many Nigerians disappointed with the perceived failures of the ruling All Progressives Congress in the country. Nazif made his position known in a statement on Wednesday. He congratulated governors of Adamawa State, Alhaji Ahmadu Fintiri; Taraba State, Mr Darius Ishaku; Bauchi State, Senator Bala Mohammed;  Benue State,  Mr Samuel Ortom, and Sokoto  State, Alhaji  Aminu Tambuwal, who emerged victorious at the Supreme Court. He said although the party was “robbed of its many victories in the last polls,” it was able to recover Adamawa, Bauchi, Benue, Sokoto, Taraba, Zamfara states and the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja. He lamented the loss of the party in Plateau and Kano states at the Supreme Court and called on all party supporters to put their differences behind them and work for the unity and progress of the party for the needed change to take place. Copyright PUNCH.
